sentence.Network_en: I once bought a thingummy out of one of those catalogues.
sentence.Network_cn: 我曾经买过那些目录里的一样东西。

PerfectNetExp.abs: thingumbob 某人thingummy 某人think a lot of 看重

derivation.yuyuan_name: late 18th cent.: from thing + a meaningless suffix

entry.tran: (指代不知其名或不愿用确切词汇或固有名称指称的人或物)那人，那东西，某某
entry.def: You refer to something or someone as thingummy ,thingummyjig or thingummybob when you do not know or cannot be bothered to use the proper word or name for them.

example.ex: I once bought a thingummy out of one of those catalogues...
example.tran: 我曾经买过那些目录里的一样东西。

example.ex: I must say, I mean, it sounded like er thingummyjig all over again without the politics.
example.tran: 我得说，我的意思是，没有了政治后，那一切听上去又像，嗯，那个什么什么了。

means.word_mean: 1. something whose name is either forgotten or not known
